<tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><img border="0" src="../triangle.JPG"><font size="3" face="Tahoma" color="#004242"><b>GRIFFON HUNTING FOR DRUID AND FRIENDS</b></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Group / Solo:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Group</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Mob Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">33 to 37</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Zone:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Karana, North</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Location:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Near the guard tower by the gypsy camp</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Character Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">29 to 40</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Strategy:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Believe it or not, but Griffon's can be killed by two Druids, or a Druid and a friend at level 29!  Having more will make it much easier, but it CAN be done! You may need to be higher level to take the higher end Griffons (if they vary in level, I'm not completely sure on that).
<br><br>
First, don't even worry about your damage shields... if it starts hitting you, run! 
<br><br>
The strategy is quite simple, actually. First, the druid casts snare to slow the sucker down (which is quite weird since its flying, wouldn't it stop it?).  Then, cast the current Animal Fear spell (surprising how many people forget Griffons are animals!).
<br><br>
So, now that you have this slow moving Griffon heading for the hills, send in the cavalry... or your single buddy you brought along! Just keep enough mana for another snare and fear, and perhaps a heal!
<br><br>
It will get much easier once you get past level 29, if you start there.  I died a few times, and not sure it was really worth it, but MAN was it fun!  I recommend a rogue as the second party member, with all those nice back stabs, or any other high damage output party member works nice.  Just be careful when the fear wears off!</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Author:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">wyndorn (Innoruuk)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rating:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>6.4</b> (average of <b>5</b> votes)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rate this spot:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><FORM ACTION = "ratehg.asp" METHOD = post><SELECT NAME="Voting"><OPTION VALUE="0">Rate this Spot</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="1">1 - Don't even bother</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="2">2</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="3">3</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="4">4</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="5">5 - It is ok</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="6">6</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="7">7</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="8">8</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="9">9</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="10">10 - You must come here</OPTION></SELECT><INPUT TYPE = "hidden" NAME = "intHGID" VALUE = 113><INPUT TYPE = "submit" VALUE="Rate It!"></form></font></td></tr>